results.title: Jungfrukallan = The Virgin Spring
results.brief_description: Bergman won his first Academy Award for this brooding medieval tale based in an old Swedish ballad, closely comparable with the ‘Seventh seal’, examining the conflict between Christianity and pagnism rife throughout the Middle Ages. Set in beautiful 14th Century Sweden, it is the sombre, powerful fable of peasant parents (Max Von Sydow and Birgitta Valberg) whose daughter, a young virgin is brutally raped and murdered by swineherds after her half sister has invoked a pagan curse. By a bizarre twist of fate the murderers ask for food and shelter from the dead girl’s parents, who, discovering the truth about their lodgers, exact a chilling revenge. A cruel and sensational allegory, a tale of superstition, religious fervour, muurder and revenge, the formal simplicity and overt symbolism conspire to create an extraordinary metaphysical charge, aided by the the luminous, haunting black and white photography and Bergman’s meticulous direction.

results.title: Jumpin' Jack Flash (Captioned)
results.creator_credit: Penny Marshall, Joel Silver, Lawrence Gordon and Twentieth Century-Fox Film Corporation
results.brief_description: Whoopi Goldberg stars in this action adventure comedy hit. There’s music, murder, mayhem and a lot of laughs as she tries to save an endangered spy operative, code-named Jack - even though she’s never met him! Now the CIA and the KGB have her jumpin’ and the world may never be the same.

results.title: Jump jet
results.creator_credit: Derek Smith and British Broadcasting Corporation
results.brief_description: The aeroplane was invented in the early 1900s. Since then there have been only three major breakthroughs in aviation: the jet, the helicopter, and the jump jet. Traces the development of the vertical take-off jet in Britain, with some reference to developments in other countries. Narrated by Richard Maddock.

results.title: Jumanji [DVD]
results.creator_credit: Joe Johnston, William Teitler, Scott Kroopf and Tri-Star Pictures
results.brief_description: For 26 years Adrian Parrish has been trapped inside an ancient board game called Jumanji. The two children who release him also unwittingly unleash a group of wild jungle creatures who go on a rampage. Alan must save his hometown from destruction or risk being exiled back into the game. Cast includes Robin Williams as Adrian Parrish.

results.title: Juliette et L'air du Temps = Juliet and the Feel of the Time
results.brief_description:
Eighteen-year old Juliette who grew up in a rural area in France has come to Paris to live. She scrapes by through begging, lives in a condemned building, and steals food occasionally at supermarkets. Her boyfriend would like her to settle down and get married, but Juliette seems to enjoy this hand-to-mouth existence.

Credits: Producer, Michel Chanderli ; director, Rene Gilson ; writer, Rene Gilson ; photography, Walter Baal ; music, Bernard Gilson.
Cast: Agnes Chateau, Jacques Zanetti, Mathieu Volta, Fabienne Arel, Janine Molinier.
